President Donald J. Trump, Vice President Mike Pence, and Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos recently held a meeting with students, teachers, and community leaders to discuss school safety. The goal of the meeting was to gain important perspectives on how to improve safety in schools across the country. Participants included individuals from the Parkland, Florida community, as well as leaders from organizations focused on preventing gun-related deaths. The discussion covered topics such as violence reduction and access to resources in schools. Many participants emphasized the need to move past partisan politics and work towards finding solutions together. In the days following the Parkland shooting, President Trump expressed support for efforts to improve the federal background check system and ensure the safety of American children.